subsection.def:
Chairman
                    (主席) means the Chairman of the Appeal Board
                appointed under section 26(2);

country
                    (國家) includes any state, province or any
                territorial entity or part which partly comprises the country;

function
                    (職能) includes power and duty, and performance
                of a function includes exercise of a power and discharge of a duty;

register
                    (註冊紀錄冊) means the register kept in accordance
                with section 7;

Registrar
                    (處長) means the Registrar of Non-local Higher
                and Professional Education Courses;

subparagraph.content:
will qualify the person who so sits, passes or undergoes for the
                            award of any higher academic qualification by a non-local institution;
                            or

will be recognized as the fulfilment of any condition for the
                            purpose of the award of any higher academic qualification by a non-local
                            institution;

the course is conducted by a non-local institution or non-local
                        professional body which mainly operates in a country outside Hong Kong in
                        collaboration with that local institution of higher education;

that professional body is generally recognized in that country
                                as an authoritative and representative professional body in the
                                relevant profession;

paragraph.content:
in the case of a course which is being conducted at the commencement date
                    appointed under section 1(2), within 1 month after such commencement
                    date;

in case such person is an individual, it is delivered to him or sent by
                    post to him at the address at which he ordinarily resides or carries on business
                    or, if such an address is unknown, at his last known address;
